  "description": "Works to a Tree with a TPO:  \rT1 (Horse Chestnut) - Remove\rT2 & T3 (Horse Chestnut) - Repollard and repeat at 2-year intervals for a period of 10 years.\rReasons:\ra.\tThe property has been the subject of movement which engineers consider to be attributable to the role of vegetation on an underlying clay soil.\rb.\tSite investigations confirm the clay soil and levels of desiccation which support the view trees are of influence.\rc.\tThe onset timing of damage is wholly consistent with the potential that it is caused by tree(s).\rd.\tLevel monitoring is supportive of the view vegetation is causal.\re.\tThe tree identified for removal is the largest/ closest vegetation to the affected part of the building. It is hoped that its removal will mitigate the influence and facilitate the retention of other surveyed trees. \rf.\tPruning to T2 & T3 seeks to establish a managed canopy framework allow future pruning works which will seek to retain the trees in a managed form. \r",
